(270, '<p>No</p>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Requests ability to condition Medicaid eligibility for non-disabled parents/caretakers relatives2 ages 19-64 on work/CE requirements</li>\r\n	<li>Individuals subject to requirements must participate in &ge;20 hours/week of work/CE activities (e.g., subsidized or unsubsidized employment, education, vocational training, job search or job skills training sponsored by the Tennessee Department of Labor and Workforce Development, accredited homeschooling, volunteering in approved settings, participation in SNAP/TANF work requirements)</li>\r\n	<li>Proposed exempt populations include: individuals physically or mentally unable to work; medically frail individuals; individuals with a disability or acute medical condition certified by a physician that prevents them from working; individuals in active SUD residential treatment; primary caregivers of a child under age six (limited to one caregiver per household); caregivers of a household member with a disability, incapacitation, or medical frailty; individuals receiving unemployment benefits; individuals recently impacted by a catastrophic event (e.g., natural disaster)</li>\r\n	<li>Individuals who fail to comply with work/CE requirements for four months in a six-month period have their benefits suspended unless they meet a good cause exemption (e.g., individuals experiencing homelessness, victims of domestic violence, victims of human trafficking, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li>Individuals may re-activate suspended coverage by meeting requirements for one month; state is considering whether to permit re-activation if an individual participates in a state-approved health or financial literacy course</li>\r\n	<li>State may temporarily suspend requirements for individuals residing in counties that are determined to be &ldquo;economically distressed&rdquo;</li>\r\n	<li>Outside of demonstration, State intends to seek federal approval to use TANF funds to provide workforce supports to individuals subject to work requirement</li>\r\n</ul>', 21, 7, '2019-03-26 08:33:02', '2019-03-26 08:33:02', NULL, NULL),
