(16, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Most recent waiver amendment approved on 2/1/2018; demonstration effective 12/16/2016 through 6/30/2021</li>\r\n	<li>Waiver amendment request with SUD features submitted to CMS on 5/25/2018; undergoing CMS review</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 4, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:36:06', '2018-11-03 06:36:06'),
(17, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Most recent waiver amendment, which includes SUD features, approved on 7/17/2018;demonstration effective 1/9/2017 through 12/31/2021</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 5, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:38:51', '2018-11-03 06:38:51'),
(18, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Demonstration authorizes state&rsquo;s mandatory MMC program</li>\r\n	<li>Waiver amendment request includes SUD features aligned with November 2017 SMD letter; state proposes offering a full continuum of SUD services and seeks a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 4, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:40:23', '2018-11-03 06:40:23'),
(19, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Delivery system demonstration authorizing the state&rsquo;s DSRIP initiative, among other features</li>\r\n	<li>DSRIP initiative includes projects targeted toward the integration of physical and behavioral health services and strategies to address the opioid crisis; projects focusing on physical/behavioral health integration are part of the state&rsquo;s strategy for transitioning to integrated managed care products by 2020; lead entities are nonprofit organizations convening providers, behavioral health agencies, and CBOs</li>\r\n	<li>Provides federal matching funds for behavioral health-related DSHPs</li>\r\n	<li>Aligns with November 2017 SMD letter; state provides a full continuum of SUD benefitsand has obtained a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 5, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:40:45', '2018-11-03 06:40:45'),
(20, '<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Integrated MMC products: Majority of Medicaid population</li>\r\n	<li>FFS: Qualified Medicare Beneficiaries and specified low-income Medicare beneficiaries (outside the demonstration)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 4, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:41:56', '2018-11-03 06:41:56'),
(21, '<p>Varies by region:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Integrated MMC products: Enrollees in two regions of the state; ASO covers SUD crisis services</li>\r\n	<li>In these regions, populations excluded from managed care (e.g., dual eligibles, medically needy, individuals in an IMD, and long-term care residents) obtain SUD services through BH limited-benefit PIHPs</li>\r\n	<li>BH limited-benefit PIHPs: Majority of Medicaid population, with the exception of enrollees living in regions with integrated MMC products</li>\r\n	<li>FFS: AI/AN population</li>\r\n	<li>State has released an RFP to procure integrated managed care products for remaining regions by 2020</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 5, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:42:00', '2018-11-03 06:42:00'),
(22, '<p>Not specified</p>', NULL, 4, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:42:24', '2018-11-03 06:42:24'),
(23, '<p>Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Requests waiver for SUD for stays up to 30 days per admission</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 4, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:43:22', '2018-11-03 06:43:22'),
(24, '<ul>\r\n	<li>SBIRT</li>\r\n	<li>Outpatient services (ASAM 1)*</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1)*</li>\r\n	<li>Residential services, including intensive inpatient services, recovery house services, longterm residential services, and youth residential services (ASAM 3.1 and 3.5)*</li>\r\n	<li>Sub-acute detoxification (ASAM 3.2-WM)*</li>\r\n	<li>Acute detoxification (ASAM 3.7-WM)*</li>\r\n	<li>Acute hospital detoxification (ASAM 4-WM)*</li>\r\n	<li>MAT/opioid treatment program*</li>\r\n	<li>MAT/office-based opioid treatment program*</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 5, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:44:33', '2018-11-03 06:44:33'),
(25, '<p>N/A</p>', NULL, 4, 10, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:44:34', '2018-11-03 06:44:34'),
(26, '<p>Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtained waiver for SUD</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 5, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:45:04', '2018-11-03 06:45:04'),
(27, '<p>Demonstration Approval; Waiver Amendment Application</p>', NULL, 4, 11, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:45:05', '2018-11-03 06:45:05'),
(28, '<p>See key SUD-related provisions above</p>', NULL, 5, 10, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:45:44', '2018-11-03 06:45:44'),
(29, '<p>Demonstration Approval and SUD Implementation Plan; Washington State Health Care<br />\r\nAuthority RFP 2019/2020 Integrated Managed Care; 1915(b) Washington State Integrated<br />\r\nCommunity Behavioral Health Program Waiver; Apple Health Managed Care</p>', NULL, 5, 11, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:46:03', '2018-11-03 06:46:03'),
(30, '<p>Waiver amendment with SUD features approved on 9/22/2017; demonstration effective<br />\r\n1/12/2015 through 12/31/2019</p>', NULL, 6, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:48:36', '2018-11-03 06:48:36'),
(80, '<p>BH-focused demonstration with two primary components:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GAP: Expands limited Medicaid benefits to childless adults and noncustodial parents with SMI ages 21&ndash;64 with incomes up to 100% FPL</li>\r\n	<li>ARTS: Implements SUD features aligned with July 2015 SMD letter; state provides a full continuum of SUD benefits and has obtained a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 6, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 06:49:25', '2018-11-03 06:49:25'),
(81, 'Waiver request submitted to CMS on 1/31/2018', 'undergoing CMS review', 13, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(82, '<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;BH-focused waiver request focused on expansion of SUD and MH benefits for three target\npopulations:</li>                                                                o Population #1: Children, adolescents, and parents/caretakers with or at risk of a MH\ndisorder or SUD\no Population #2: Individuals ages 18-64 with acute MH needs\no Population #3: Adolescents and adults ages 12-64 with SUDs\n	<li>Proposes offering enhanced SUD and/or MH benefits for covered populations</li>   <li>Includes SUD features aligned with November 2017 SMD letter; state proposes offering a\nfull continuum of SUD services and seeks a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\n</ul>', '', 13, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(83, '<ul><li>FFS administered by ASO: New enhanced BH services covered through demonstration\n(state has not yet contracted with ASO)\n</li> <li> FFS: All other BH services (outside the demonstration)</li>', '', 13, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(84, '<p>Proposed enhanced benefits include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Community and recovery support services^</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive case management services^</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile crisis response services^</li>\r\n	<li>23-hour crisis stabilization services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Crisis stabilization and observation services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Crisis residential stabilization services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Peer-based crisis intervention services^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Early intervention (SBIRT)</li>\r\n	<li>MAT (ASAM 1)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Outpatient MAT care coordination^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence-based screenings and assessments (ASAM 0.5)^</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1) (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Residential treatment services (including ASAM 3.3)^</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed high-intensity residential services--adults (ASAM 3.5)</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed medium-intensity services--youth (ASAM 3.5)^</li>\r\n	<li>Ambulatory withdrawal management without extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 1- WM)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Ambulatory withdrawal management with extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 2-WM)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 13, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-05 07:08:12'),
(85, 'Yes\n&#8226; Requests waiver for MH and SUD ', '', 13, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(86, 'Seeks to offer enhanced MH benefit package, including MH day treatment, ACT, and\ntherapeutic foster care services, for populations #1 and #2 ', '', 13, 10, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(87, 'Original Waiver Application', '', 13, 11, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(88, '<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;Most recent waiver amendment (without SUD features) approved on 12/29/2017; demonstration effective 10/1/2016 through 9/30/2021</li>\n	<li>Waiver amendment request with SUD features submitted to CMS on 5/3/2017; undergoing CMS review</li>\n</ul>', '', 14, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(89, '<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;Most recent waiver amendment (without SUD features) approved on 12/29/2017; demonstration effective 10/1/2016 through 9/30/2021</li>\n	<li>Waiver amendment request with SUD features submitted to CMS on 5/3/2017; undergoing CMS review</li>\n</ul>', '', 14, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(90, '<ul> <li>  Integrated MMC plans: Majority of Medicaid population</li>\n<li> FFS: AI/AN population that opts out of managed care</li></ul>', '', 14, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(91, '<p>Proposed enhanced benefits include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Community and recovery support services^</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive case management services^</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile crisis response services^</li>\r\n	<li>23-hour crisis stabilization services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Crisis stabilization and observation services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Crisis residential stabilization services^ (population #1 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Peer-based crisis intervention services^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Early intervention (SBIRT) ï‚§ MAT (ASAM 1)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>Outpatient MAT care coordination^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Evidence-based screenings and assessments (ASAM 0.5)^</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1) (population #3 only) ï‚§ Residential treatment services (including ASAM 3.3)^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Clinically managed high-intensity residential services&mdash;adults (ASAM 3.5)^</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed medium-intensity services&mdash;youth (ASAM 3.5)^</li>\r\n	<li>Ambulatory withdrawal management without extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 1- WM)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Ambulatory withdrawal management with extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 2-WM)^ (population #3 only)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 14, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-05 07:15:25'),
(92, 'Yes\n<ul><li> Requests waiver for BH; does not specify if request applies to both SUD and MH services</li></ul>', '', 14, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(93, 'Approved demonstration authorizes specialized, integrated managed care products for\nenrollees with SMI', '', 14, 10, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(94, 'Demonstration Approval Waiver Amendment Application', '', 14, 11, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(95, '<ul><li> Most recent waiver amendment (without SUD features) approved on 12/22/2017;\ndemonstration effective 12/30/2015 through 12/31/2020</li>\n<li> Waiver amendment with SUD features approved on 8/13/2015</li></ul>', '', 15, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(96, '<ul><li> Delivery system reform demonstration that authorizes, among other features:\no SUD initiative called Drug Medi-Cal Organized Delivery System (DMC-ODS), which\naligns with July 2015 SMD letter; State provides a full continuum of SUD benefits and\nhas obtained a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\n<li> DMC-ODS provides both State Plan benefits and benefits newly authorized under\nthe demonstration</li>\n<li> Counties have the option of participating in DMC-ODS\n</li><li> The full range of DMS-ODS benefits (see below) are only available to Medicaid\nenrollees<li> residing in a participating county; the more limited State Plan SUD\nbenefit package is available in non-participating counties\no Public Hospital Redesign & Incentives in Medi-Cal (PRIME), a follow-up to State???s DSRIP\ninitiative authorized under an earlier version of the demonstration</li>\n<li> Includes projects to be implemented through designated public hospital systems\nand district/municipal public hospitals targeted toward addressing primary\ncare/behavioral health integration\no Whole Person Care (WPC) Pilots</li>\n<li> Designed to coordinate physical health, behavioral health, and social services\nthrough collaboration among county agencies, health plans, and providers with a\nfocus on vulnerable populations</li>\n<li> May be led by a city, a county, a city and county, a health or hospital authority, or\na consortium of cities, counties, and/or health or hospital authorities\n</li> <li> Provide access to interventions that would not otherwise be covered by Medicaid\n(e.g., tenancy-based care management services, county housing pools to support\nmedically necessary housing services, etc.)\n</li><li> May select individuals with SUDs or MH disorders as a target population</li>', '', 15, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(97, '&#8226;  County-operated BH limited-benefit PIHPs: All DMC-ODS benefits in DMC-ODS\nparticipating counties\n&#8226; FFS:\no In counties that are not participating in DMC-ODS: All State Plan SUD benefits\no In counties participating in DMC-ODS: Medically monitored inpatient services,\nmedically managed intensive inpatient services, medically monitored inpatient\nwithdrawal management, medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal\nmanagement, medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal management, and\nSBIRT for populations for populations excluded from managed care (services not\ncovered by BH limited-benefit PIHPs; excluded populations vary by county)\n&#8226; MMC plans providing physical health services: In all counties, provide medically monitored\ninpatient services, medically managed intensive inpatient services, medically monitored\ninpatient withdrawal management, medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal\nManagement, medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal management, and SBIRT\n(services not covered by BH limited-benefit PIHPs) to individuals enrolled in MMC for\nphysical health services', '? Waiver amendment request includes SUD\nfeatures aligned with November 2017 SMD\nletter; state offers a full continuum of SUD\nservices and seeks a waiver of the IMD\nExclusion', 15, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(98, 'DMC-ODS benefits:<ul>\n<li> Early intervention (SBIRT) (ASAM 0.5)</li>\n<li> Outpatient drug-free treatment services (ASAM 1)</li>\n<li> Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1)</li>\n<li> Partial hospitalization (optional; counties do not have to offer service) (ASAM 2.5)^</li>\n<li> Residential treatment services: counties are initially required to provide at least one of the\nASAM levels below; within three years, they must provide all ASAM levels\no Clinically managed low-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.1)^*\no Clinically managed population-specific high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.3)^*\no Clinically managed high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.5)^*\n<li> Withdrawal management services: counties are required to provide at least one of the\nfollowing ASAM levels</li>\no Ambulatory withdrawal management without extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 1-\nWM)\no Ambulatory withdrawal management with extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 2-WM)\no Clinically managed residential withdrawal management (ASAM 3.2-WM)\n<li> Medically monitored inpatient services (ASAM 3.7) (provided via MMC plan or FFS)*</li>\n<li> Medically managed intensive inpatient services (ASAM 4) (provided via MMC plan or FFS)*</li>\n<li> Medically monitored inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 3.7-WM) (provided via\nMMC plan or FFS)*</li>\n<li> Medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 4-WM) (provided\nvia MMC plan or FFS)*</li>\n<li> Narcotic treatment program/opioid treatment program (methadone, buprenorphine,\ndisulfiram, and naloxone)</li>\n<li> MAT</li>\n<li> Recovery services^</li>\n<li> Case management^</li>\n<li> Physician consultation</li></ul>\nState Plan benefits:\n<ul><li> Early intervention (SBIRT) (ASAM 0.5)</li>\n<li> Outpatient drug-free treatment services (ASAM 1)</li>\n<li> Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1)</li>\n<li> Residential treatment services (for perinatal population only)</li>\n<li> Medically monitored inpatient services (ASAM 3.7)</li>\n<li> Medically managed intensive inpatient services (ASAM 4)</li>\n<li> Medically monitored inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 3.7-WM)</li>\n<li> Medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 4-WM)</li>\n<li> Narcotic treatment program (methadone only)</li>\n<li> MAT</li>\n<li> Targeted case management (not available statewide)</li>', '', 15, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(99, 'Yes <ul><li>Obtained waiver for SUD for counties participating in DMC-ODS</li>  <li>Length of stay limited to two nonconsecutive 90-day stays per year for adults and two\nnonconsecutive 30-day stays per year for adolescents; length of stay for criminal justice\noffenders can be up to six consecutive months </li></ul>', '', 15, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
