(102, '<ul> <li>  Most recent waiver amendment (without SUD features) approved on 12/20/2017 demonstration effective 9/30/2013 through\n12/31/2018</li><li>Waiver amendment with SUD features\napproved on 12/19/2014</li></ul>', '<ul><li> Waiver amendment with SUD features\nsubmitted to CMS on 6/29/2018;\nundergoing CMS review</li></ul>', 16, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(103, '<ul><li> Demonstration authorizes State\'s mandatory MMC program, among other features </li><li> Waiver features include Promoting Optimal\nMental Health for Individuals through\nSupports and Empowerment (PROMISE), an\ninitiative targeted toward individuals who\nhave an SPMI or SUD and require HCBS "to\nlive and work in integrated settings" </li> <li>Individuals enrolled in PROMISE have access to enhanced MH, SUD, and HCBS benefits and a Division of Substance Abuse and Mental Health case manager </li><li> MMC plans must ensure coordination between FFS PROMISE benefits and BH benefits provided through MMC plans</li></ul>', '<ul><li> Waiver amendment request includes SUD\nfeatures aligned with November 2017 SMD\nletter; state offers a full continuum of SUD\nservices and seeks a waiver of the IMD\nExclusion</li></ul>', 16, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(104, '<ul><li>  Integrated MMC plans: State Plan BH benefits for majority of Medicaid population </li> <li> FFS: o PROMISE enhanced BH benefits for individuals eligible for PROMISE (within demonstration) o All State Plan BH benefits for populations excluded from managed care, including individuals enrolled in PACE, individuals residing in an ICF/IID, and individuals in the State\'s I/DD 1915(c) waiver (outside the demonstration)</li></ul>', 'No proposed changes', 16, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
(105, 'PROMISE enhanced benefits for individuals\nwith SUD include:<ul><li> Benefits counseling^</li>\n<li> Case management^</li>\n<li> Community-based residential alternative\nsupports that exclude assisted living^ </li><li> Community transition services^</li>\n<li> Financial coaching^</li>\n<li> Non-medical transportation^</li>\n<li> Nursing^</li>\n<li> Peer supports^</li>\n<li> Personal care^</li>\n<li> Respite^</li>\n<li> Skill-building for individual activities of daily\nliving/chores^</li>\n<li> Supported employment (both individual and\nsmall group)^\nOther benefits include:</li>\n<li> MAT</li>\n<li> Services delivered by BH practitioner</li>', 'State provides full continuum of SUD services,\nincluding:\n<ul><li> Crisis intervention</li>\n<li> Outpatient addiction treatment, including\nMAT</li>\n<li> Residential addiction treatment services</li></ul>', 16, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:10', '2018-11-03 09:43:10'),
