(124, '<ul><li> BH-focused demonstration that authorizes nine BH- and HCBS-related pilot programs</li>\n<li> Aligns with November 2017 SMD letter; state provides a full continuum of SUD benefits</li>\nand has obtained a waiver of the IMD exclusion\n<li> Provides expenditure authority to implement the following SUD- and/or MH-related pilots</li>\n<p>(pilots have capped enrollment and may not operate statewide):</p>\n<p>o Clinically managed withdrawal management services pilot: Covers clinically managed\nwithdrawal management services for up to 11,072 enrollees</p>\n<p> o SUD case management pilot: Covers SUD case management services for up to 2,835\nenrollees who qualify for diversion from the criminal justice system<p>\n<p>o Peer recovery support services pilot: Covers peer support services delivered by a\nrecovery coach for up to 320 enrollees with a SUD</p>\n<p>o Crisis intervention services pilot: Covers crisis intervention services delivered at acute\ncare hospitals, PRTFs, or community residential treatment centers with <16 beds for up\nto 8,493 enrollees who are experiencing psychiatric crisis</p>\n<p>o Evidence-based home visiting services pilot: Covers evidence-based home visits\ndelivered by mental health professionals for up to 1,038 children up to age 5 who were\nborn with withdrawal symptoms and for mothers up to 60 days postpartum whose\nchildren have withdrawal symptoms</p>\n<p>o Assistance in community integration services pilot: Covers pre-tenancy supports and\ntenancy-sustaining services for up to 3,750 enrollees who have a significant number of\nED visits/hospitalizations or two or more chronic conditions and are â€œat imminent riskâ€\nof homelessness or institutionalization</p>\n<p>o Supported employment services pilot: Covers pre-employment services (e.g., personcentered\nemployment planning, pre-vocational/job-related discovery or assessment,\netc.) and employment-sustaining services (e.g., career advancement services, job\ncoaching, etc.) for up to 3,375 enrollees with serious and persistent MH needs or SUD\nneeds</p>\n<p>o Intensive in-home services pilot: Covers intensive in-home services for up to 18,650\nenrollees ages 3â€“21 who meet the stateâ€™s health home eligibility criteria and have\nsignificant BH needs</p>\n<p>o Respite services pilot: Covers respite services for up to 3,871 enrollees ages 3â€“21 who\nhave significant MH needs </p></ul>', '', 19, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:11', '2018-11-03 09:43:11'),
(125, '<ul><li> Integrated MMC plans: Majority of Medicaid population</li>\n<li> FFS: Populations excluded from MMC, including AI/AN population and dual eligibles</li></ul>', '', 19, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 09:43:11', '2018-11-03 09:43:11'),
