(195, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Varies by populationEnrollees required to enroll in managed care choose one of the following options for BH services:&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; o Integrated MMC plan</p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;o Integrated ACO</p>\r\n   <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;o BH limited-benefit PIHP</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>FFS: Populations excluded from managed care, including individuals ages 65+ and individuals enrolled in PACE (outside the demonstration, with the exception of certain services delivered to individuals in IMDs)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 29, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 10:53:40', '2018-11-03 10:53:40'),
(196, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Community support program^</li>\r\n	<li>Acute treatment services for substance abuse^*</li>\r\n	<li>Clinical support services for substance abuse^*</li>\r\n	<li>Structured outpatient addiction program^</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient program^</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed low-intensity residential services, including 24-hour transitional support services, 24-hour residential rehabilitation services, and 24-hour communitybased family SUD treatment services (ASAM 3.1)^*</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed population-specific high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.3)^*</li>\r\n	<li>Recovery support navigator services^</li>\r\n	<li>Recovery coach services^ (available to ACO/MCO enrollees only)</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient program^</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 29, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 10:55:29', '2018-11-03 10:55:29'),
(197, '<p>Waiver request with SUD features submitted to CMS on 11/20/2017; undergoing CMS review</p>', NULL, 30, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 10:58:19', '2018-11-03 10:58:19'),
(198, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Demonstration seeks to implement mandatory MMC for the majority of the Medicaid population, among other features</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Seeks to create specialized managed care products for enrollees with significant BH needs, I/DDs, and TBIs that are called behavioral health and intellectual/developmental disability (BH I/DD) tailored plans</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Proposes including SUD features aligned with November 2017 SMD letter; state proposes offering a full continuum of SUD services and seeks a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\r\n	<li>Requests comparability waiver to offer more intensive BH benefits, including intensive SUD residential services, only to individuals in BH I/DD tailored plans</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Seeks expenditure authority to provide funding to support BH I/DD tailored plans, care management agencies, and providers build capacity (e.g., IT and workforce) to implement BH and I/DD-focused health homes</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 30, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 10:59:37', '2018-11-03 10:59:37'),
(199, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Years 1 and 2 of managed care implementation:</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Integrated MMC plans (standard plans): Majority of Medicaid population</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;BH limited-benefit PIHPs: Qualifying individuals with SMI, SED, SUD, I/DD or TBI; HCBS waiver enrollees; dual eligibles; and medically needy individuals</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;FFS: Populations excluded from BH limited-benefit PIHPs, including children enrolled in CHIP with significant BH needs and legal aliens (outside the demonstration, with the exception of services provided to individuals in IMDs)</li>\r\n	<li>Years 3+ of managed care implementation:</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Integrated MMC plans (standard plans and BH I/DD tailored plans): Majority of Medicaid population, including qualifying individuals (including children enrolled in CHIP) with SMI, SED, SUD, or I/DD</li>\r\n	<li>FFS: Populations excluded from managed care, including medically needy individuals, certain HCBS waiver enrollees, and dual eligibles without significant BH needs or an I/DD (outside the demonstration, with the exception of services provided to individuals in IMDs)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 30, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:00:43', '2018-11-03 11:00:43'),
(200, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Substance abuse halfway house (ASAM 3.1)*</li>\r\n	<li>Social setting detoxification (ASAM 3.2-WM)*</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Clinically managed population-specific high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.3)* (BH I/DD tailored plans only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Substance abuse nonmedical community residential treatment (ASAM 3.5)* (BH I/DD tailored plans only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Substance abuse medically monitored community residential treatment (ASAM 3.7)*</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Nonhospital medical detoxification (ASAM 3.7 WM)* (BH I/DD tailored plans only)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Medically supervised or alcohol drug abuse treatment center (ADATC) detoxification crisis stabilization (ASAM 3.9-WM)*</li>\r\n	<li>Medically managed intensive inpatient services (ASAM 4)*</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 30, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:01:50', '2018-11-03 11:01:50'),
(201, '<p>Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Requests waiver for SUD and MH</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 30, 9, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:02:08', '2018-11-03 11:02:08'),
(202, '<p>Yes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtained waiver for MH and SUD limited to the services listed below:6 o Acute treatment services for substance abuse^*</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;o Clinical support services for substance abuse^*</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; o Transitional care unit services^*</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; o Clinically managed low-intensity residential services, including 24-hour transitional&nbsp; support services, 24-hour residential rehabilitation services, and 24-hour community-based family SUD treatment services (ASAM 3.1)^*</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;o Clinically managed population-specific high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.3)^*</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Waiver funding is authorized through Safety Net Care Pool and is capped</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 29, 5, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:02:15', '2018-11-03 11:03:12'),
(203, '<p>See information above regarding BH I/DD tailored plans</p>', NULL, 30, 10, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:02:54', '2018-11-03 11:02:54'),
