(209, '<ul>\r\n	<li>BH- and I/DD-focused waiver request seeking to combine authority for 1915(b) and 1915(c) waivers related to the delivery of BH and HCBS benefits</li>\r\n	<li>Includes SUD features aligned with July 2015 SMD letter, proposes offering a full continuum of SUD benefits, and seeks a waiver of the IMD exclusion</li>\r\n	<li>Seeks expenditure authority to implement alternative payment methodologies that promote physical and BH integration between PIHPs providing BH services and MMC plans providing physical health, acute care, and pharmacy services</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 32, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:20:29', '2018-11-03 11:20:29'),
(210, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Demonstration authorizes state&rsquo;s mandatory MMC program, DSRIP initiative, and specialized managed care products for adults ages 21+ with SMI or serious SUD (called Health and Recovery Plans, or HARPs), among other features</li>\r\n	<li>HARP enrollees have access to an enhanced BH benefit package; benefits are tiered based on an enrollee&rsquo;s level of need</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Utilization of enhanced HARP services is subject to an annual dollar cap</li>\r\n	<li>DSRIP initiative includes projects targeted toward addressing primary care/BH integration and preventing substance abuse; safety net hospitals are lead entities and form networks of providers and CBOs</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Seeks to carve BH benefits into integrated<br />\r\nMMC plans for individuals ages &lt;21 (see<br />\r\nadditional detail below)8</p>', 31, 6, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:20:32', '2018-11-03 11:20:54'),
(211, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Integrated MMC plans: Majority of Medicaid population ages 21+</li>\r\n	<li>FFS: Individuals ages &lt;21 (within demonstration) and populations excluded from managed care, including spend-down populations and individuals receiving partial benefits, among others (outside of demonstration)</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeks to transition SUD and MH benefits for individuals ages &lt;21 from FFS to integrated MMC plans; individuals ages &lt;21 will not enroll in HARP</li>\r\n	<li>Individuals who are excluded or exempt from managed care, including foster care children in the placement of a voluntary agency and individuals age &lt;21 who are permanent residents of residential healthcare facilities, will continue to receive SUD services through FFS</li>\r\n</ul>', 31, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:22:12', '2018-11-03 11:22:12'),
(212, '<ul>\r\n	<li>BH limited-benefit PIHP: Majority of Medicaid population for most SUD services</li>\r\n	<li>MMC plans providing physical health, acute care, and pharmacy services: Majority of Medicaid population for inpatient SUD treatment (ASAM 4 and ASAM 4-WM) ï‚§ FFS: All SUD services for populations excluded from managed care, such as individuals in a nursing facility or ICF/IID (outside the demonstration)</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 32, 7, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:23:00', '2018-11-03 11:23:00'),
(213, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Early intervention (ASAM 0.5) ï‚§ Outpatient therapy (ASAM 1)</li>\r\n	<li>Intensive outpatient services (ASAM 2.1)</li>\r\n	<li>Partial hospitalization (ASAM 2.5)</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed low-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.1)</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed population-specific high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.3)</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed high-intensity residential services (ASAM 3.5)</li>\r\n	<li>Medically monitored intensive inpatient services (ASAM 3.7)</li>\r\n	<li>Medically managed intensive inpatient services (ASAM 4)</li>\r\n	<li>Ambulatory withdrawal management without extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 1-WM)</li>\r\n	<li>Ambulatory withdrawal management with extended on-site monitoring (ASAM 2-WM)</li>\r\n	<li>Clinically managed residential withdrawal management (ASAM 3.2-WM)</li>\r\n	<li>Medically monitored inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 3.7-WM)</li>\r\n	<li>Medically managed intensive inpatient withdrawal management (ASAM 4-WM)</li>\r\n	<li>Opioid treatment program, including MAT</li>\r\n	<li>Targeted case management</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 32, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:24:59', '2018-11-03 11:24:59'),
(214, '<ul>\r\n	<li>HARP enhanced benefits include:</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;BH HCBS assessment^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Empowerment services&mdash;peer supports^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Habilitation services^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Nonmedical transportation^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Family support and training^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Employment supports^</li>\r\n	<li>Other benefits include:</li>\r\n	<li>Inpatient and outpatient BH services, including chemical dependency services</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Residential addiction services^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Outpatient addiction services^</li>\r\n	<li>Crisis intervention^</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Licensed BH practitioner services^</li>\r\n	<li>Medically supervised outpatient withdrawal</li>\r\n	<li>Office of Alcoholism and Substance Abuse Services (OASAS) outpatient and opioid treatment program services</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;OASAS outpatient rehabilitation programs</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Inpatient hospital: Medically managed detoxification (hospital-based)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Inpatient hospital: Medically supervised inpatient detoxification</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Residential rehabilitation services for youth<br />\r\n(carved out of managed care)</p>', 31, 8, NULL, NULL, '2018-11-03 11:26:01', '2018-11-03 11:26:01'),
