(49, '<p>Actual acquisition cost.</p>', '<p>$12 dispensing fee when billed with UD modifier $35.00 dispensing fee when billed with UD modifier for highly effective birth control methods (J3490 and J8499)</p>', '<p>Practitioner dispensing fee applies to dispensing by: &bull; Advanced Practice Nurses &bull; Dentists Providing Medical Services &bull; Encounter Rate Clinics &bull; Fee-For-Service Hospitals &bull; Imaging Centers &bull; Independent Diagnostic Testing Facilities (IDTFs) &bull; Independent Laboratories &bull; Local Health Departments &bull; Optometrists Providing Medical Services &bull; Physicians &bull; Portable X-ray Companies</p>', '<p>Handbook for Practitioners Rendering Medical Services, Ch. A-200, Policies and Procedures, &sect; A-202.1.6. Illinois Department of Healthcare and Family Services Practitioner Fee Schedule Key</p>', 9, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2018-10-09 04:22:23', '2018-11-22 04:57:37', '<p>https://www.illinois.gov/hfs/sitecollectiondocuments/a200.pdf https://www.illinois.gov/hfs/SiteCollectionDocuments/4.22.16PractitionerFeeScheduleKey.pdf</p>'),
