(53, NULL, NULL, '<p>Provider-level indicators. Providers using 340B drugs for Medicaid patients are required to report this information on the MEF. Claim-level indicators. Non-pharmacy providers must identify 340B purchased drugs by reporting modifier &ldquo;UD&rdquo; in conjunction with the appropriate drug CPT or HCPCS code. Pharmacy providers submitting claims through the point-of-sale system for drugs purchased through the 340B program must identify the drug as a 340B purchased drug by populating the Submission Clarification Code (42&Oslash;-DK) field with a value of 20. Providers are required to add the dispensing fee to the provider charge.</p>', '<p>Handbook for Practitioners Rendering Medical Services, Ch. A-200, Policies and Procedures, &sect; A-202.1.6. Illinois Department of Healthcare and Family Services Provider Notice, issued 4/15/13, re: &ldquo;$12 Dispensing Fee for 340B Purchased Drugs.&rdquo;</p>', 9, 1, 5, '1', '2', '1', '2018-10-09 04:22:24', '2018-11-22 04:58:54', '<p>https://www.illinois.gov/hfs/sitecollectiondocuments/a200.pdf https://www.illinois.gov/hfs/MedicalProviders/notices/Pages/prn130415a.aspx</p>'),
