(161, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Provider-level Indicators:</strong> MCOs must specify in applicable provider agreements that all providers who participate in the federal 340B program give TennCare MCOs the benefit of 340B pricing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Claims-based Indicators: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>340B pharmacies will be required to identify 340B claims by submitting the Submission Clarification Code (420-DK) of 20 and a Basis of Cost Determination (423-DN) of 08 &ldquo;Disproportionate Share Pricing&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It is the policy of TennCare to seek federal rebates only on pharmacy claims that are not associated with the 340B Drug Pricing Program. If a participating pharmacy provider submits a claim to TennCare at the pharmacy&#39;s 340B acquisition cost, TennCare will pay the claim in accordance with established procedures but will not submit the claim to the manufacturer to collect a federal rebate.&rdquo;</p>', '<p>TN MCO Statewide Contract 2.12.9.60 (page 288)<br />\r\nTennessee Medicaid Pharmacy Claims Submission Manual &ndash; October 2018<br />\r\nTennCare Policy Manual PRO 13-002(Rev. 2) 06/22/2016</p>', 27, 1, 11, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-17 10:46:41', '2018-11-20 11:14:06', '<p><a href="https://www.tn.gov/content/dam/tn/tenncare/documents/MCOStatewideContract.pdf">TN MCO Statewide Contract 2.12.9.60 (page 288)</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://tenncare.magellanhealth.com/static/docs/Program_Information/TN_Medicaid_Pharmacy_Claims_Submission_Manual_Final.pdf">Tennessee Medicaid Pharmacy Claims Submission Manual &ndash; October 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.tn.gov/content/dam/tn/tenncare/documents2/pro13-002.pdf">TennCare Policy Manual PRO 13-002(Rev. 2) 06/22/2016</a></p>'),
(162, NULL, NULL, '<p>MCOs must specify in applicable provider agreements that all providers who participate in the federal 340B program give TennCare MCOs the benefit of 340B pricing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Claims-based indicators: </strong>340B pharmacies will be required to identify 340B claims by submitting the Submission Clarification Code (420-DK) of 20 and a Basis of Cost Determination (423-DN) of 08 &ldquo;Disproportionate Share Pricing&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It is the policy of TennCare to seek federal rebates only on pharmacy claims that are not associated with the 340B Drug Pricing Program. If a participating pharmacy provider submits a claim to TennCare at the pharmacy&#39;s 340B acquisition cost, TennCare will pay the claim in accordance with established procedures but will not submit the claim to the manufacturer to collect a federal rebate.&rdquo;</p>', '<p>TN MCO Statewide Contract 2.12.9.60 (page 288)<br />\r\nTennessee Medicaid Pharmacy Claims Submission Manual &ndash; October 2018<br />\r\nTennCare Policy Manual PRO 13-002(Rev. 2) 06/22/2016</p>', 27, 1, 12, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-17 10:49:20', '2018-11-20 11:18:31', '<p><a href="https://www.tn.gov/content/dam/tn/tenncare/documents/MCOStatewideContract.pdf">TN MCO Statewide Contract 2.12.9.60 (page 288)</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://tenncare.magellanhealth.com/static/docs/Program_Information/TN_Medicaid_Pharmacy_Claims_Submission_Manual_Final.pdf">Tennessee Medicaid Pharmacy Claims Submission Manual &ndash; October 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.tn.gov/content/dam/tn/tenncare/documents2/pro13-002.pdf">TennCare Policy Manual PRO 13-002(Rev. 2) 06/22/2016</a></p>'),
(163, '<p>Brands and generics &minus; WAC minus 57 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) products</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &minus; Wholesale acquisition cost (WAC) minus 40 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hemophilia products &minus; WAC minus 32 percent</p>', '<p>the lesser of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. AAC plus a reasonable dispensing fee*</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The Usual and Customary (UAC) price charged the general public</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Gross Amount Due (GAD), if provided</p>', '<p>New drugs are added to the formulary at WAC minus 23.1 percent for 6 months. This methodology is not all inclusive and some products may be priced manually.1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*reasonable dispensing fee = (AAC+$7.93/0.9804 &minus; AAC)&nbsp;+ $0.50 PPG Incentive Premium preferred generic (PPG) incentive ($0.50) [only added if the pharmacy dispenses a PPG]. Does not apply to $0 total payment amount claims.</p>', '<p>1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018<br />\r\n2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</p>', 28, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 10:53:18', '2018-11-20 11:32:16', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/drug-pricing-reimbursement.pdf">2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</a></p>'),
(164, '<p>Brands and generics</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&minus; WAC minus 57 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) products</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&minus; Wholesale acquisition cost (WAC) minus 40 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hemophilia products</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &minus; WAC minus 32 percent</p>', '<p>the lesser of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. AAC plus a reasonable dispensing fee*</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The Usual and Customary (UAC) price charged the general public</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Gross Amount Due (GAD), if provided</p>', '<p>New drugs are added to the formulary at WAC minus 23.1 percent for 6 months. This methodology is not all inclusive and some products may be priced manually<sup>1</sup>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*reasonable dispensing fee = ( AAC+$7.93/ 0.9804 &minus; AAC) + $0.50 PPG Incentive Premium preferred generic (PPG) incentive ($0.50) only added if the pharmacy dispenses a PPG. Does not apply to $0 total payment amount claims.<sup>2</sup></p>', '<p>1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018<br />\r\n2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</p>', 28, 1, 2, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 10:54:37', '2018-11-20 11:29:17', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/drug-pricing-reimbursement.pdf">2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</a></p>'),
(165, 'Brands and generics âˆ’ WAC minus 57 percent Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) products âˆ’ Wholesale acquisition cost (WAC) minus 40 percent Hemophilia products âˆ’ WAC minus 32 percent', 'the lesser of the following: 1. AAC plus a reasonable dispensing fee* 2. The Usual and Customary (UAC) price charged the general public 3. The Gross Amount Due (GAD), if provided', 'New drugs are added to the formulary at WAC minus 23.1 percent for 6 months. This methodology is not all inclusive and some products may be priced manually.1 *reasonable dispensing fee = ï¿½ AAC+$7.93 0.9804 âˆ’ AACï¿½ + $0.50 PPG Incentive Premium preferred generic (PPG) incentive ($0.50) only added if the pharmacy dispenses a PPG. Does not apply to $0 total payment amount claims. 2', 'Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018', 28, 1, 3, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 10:57:08', '2018-11-17 10:57:08', 'Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018'),
(166, '<p>Brands and generics</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&minus; WAC minus 57 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) products</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &minus; Wholesale acquisition cost (WAC) minus 40 percent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hemophilia products</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&minus; WAC minus 32 percent</p>', '<p>the lesser of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. AAC plus a reasonable dispensing fee*</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The Usual and Customary (UAC) price charged the general public</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Gross Amount Due (GAD), if provided</p>', '<p>New drugs are added to the formulary at WAC minus 23.1 percent for 6 months. This methodology is not all inclusive and some products may be priced manually.1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*reasonable dispensing fee = (AAC+$7.93/0.9804 &minus; AAC)&nbsp;+ $0.50 PPG Incentive Premium preferred generic (PPG) incentive ($0.50) [only added if the pharmacy dispenses a PPG]. Does not apply to $0 total payment amount claims 2.</p>', '<p>1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018<br />\r\n2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</p>', 28, 1, 4, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 10:59:36', '2018-11-20 11:33:52', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">1. Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/drug-pricing-reimbursement.pdf">2. Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual. Pricing and Reimbursement &ndash; May 2018</a></p>'),
(167, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Provider-level indicators</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Covered entities participating in the HRSA 340B Drug Pricing Program are required to identify in the proper field of the application to denote that the entity is eligible to purchase products under through the HRSA 340B program.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Claim-level indicators:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Pharmacies of eligible entities participating in the 340B Drug Pricing Program must identify all outpatient pharmacy claims filled with 340B stock for 340B-eligible people in all programs by submitting a value of &quot;2&Oslash;&quot; (&quot;34&Oslash;B / Disproportionate Share Pricing/Public Health Service&quot;) in the &quot;Submission Clarification Code&quot; field (42&Oslash;-DK).&rdquo;</p>', '<p>Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018<br />\r\nTexas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Enrollment Application &ndash; 9.6 (page 5/13)</p>', 28, 1, 5, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-17 11:03:31', '2018-11-20 11:35:23', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/providers/pharmacy-provider-application.pdf">Texas Vendor Drug Program Pharmacy Provider Enrollment Application &ndash; 9.6 (page 5/13)</a></p>'),
(168, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Claim-level indicators:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;At the point the [contract] pharmacy is notified or discovers that the claim qualifies as a 340B claim, the original claim must be reversed and the claim resubmitted as a 340B claim with the correct &ldquo;Submission Clarification Code&rdquo; value. If the claim has not been corrected to include the correct &quot;Submission Clarification Code&quot; value, the pharmacy and the eligible entity are at risk for duplicate discounts.&rdquo;</p>', '<p>Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</p>', 28, 1, 6, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-17 11:04:59', '2018-11-20 11:35:54', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a></p>'),
(169, NULL, NULL, '<p>&ldquo;Medicaid managed care organizations (MCO) implemented their own 340B reimbursement methodologies on December 1, 2014.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;A 340B covered entity seeking to use 340B stock in Medicaid managed care must contract with the MCO as a 340B pharmacy and accept the payment terms of their &quot;shared-savings&quot; model&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;An MCO cannot require one of its network pharmacy providers to submit its actual acquisition cost (AAC) on outpatient drugs and biological products purchased through the 340B program&rdquo;</p>', '<p>Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</p>', 29, 1, 7, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 11:07:54', '2018-11-20 11:38:50', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a></p>'),
(170, NULL, NULL, '<p>&ldquo;Medicaid managed care organizations (MCO) implemented their own 340B reimbursement methodologies on December 1, 2014.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;A 340B covered entity seeking to use 340B stock in Medicaid managed care must contract with the MCO as a 340B pharmacy and accept the payment terms of their &quot;shared-savings&quot; model&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;An MCO cannot require one of its network pharmacy providers to submit its actual acquisition cost (AAC) on outpatient drugs and biological products purchased through the 340B program&rdquo;</p>', '<p>Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</p>', 29, 1, 8, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-17 11:09:15', '2018-11-20 11:38:47', '<p><a href="https://www.txvendordrug.com/sites/txvendordrug/files/docs/manuals/health-resources-services-administration.pdf">Texas Vendor Drug Program: Pharmacy Provider Procedure Manual - Health Resources and Services Administration - May 2018</a></p>'),
