(217, '<p>The lessor of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The National Average Drug Acquisition Cost Brand (NADACB) price as established by CMS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The provider&rsquo;s usual and customary charge to the public, as identified by the claim</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Federal Upper Limit (FUL) as established by CMS in 42 CFR &sect; 447.332</p>', '<p>$3.75</p>', '<p>If a National Average Drug Acquisition Cost does not exist then the drug claim shall reimburse at the lessor of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The Wholesale Acquisition Cost (WAC)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The provider&rsquo;s usual and customary charge to the public, as identified by the claim</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Federal Upper Limit (FUL as established by CMS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If neither a National Average Drug Acquisition Cost (NADAC) or a Wholesale Acquisition Cost (WAC) exists, than the claim will deny and return a message &ldquo;Drug Cost Not On File&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Only one dispensing fee per month per member for each specific drug entity with the exception of 72-hour emergency prescriptions for non-PDL drugs.</p>', '<p>Virginia Pharmacy Provider Manual &ndash; Covered Services and Limitations &ndash; October 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. 12VAC30-80-40. Feefor-service providers: pharmacy.</p>', 35, 1, 3, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-19 07:53:30', '2018-11-20 12:17:49', '<p><a href="https://www.ecm.virginiamedicaid.dmas.virginia.gov/WorkplaceXT/ContainerLogin.jsp">Virginia Pharmacy Provider Manual &ndash; Covered Services and Limitations &ndash; October 2017</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. <a href="http://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?000+reg+12VAC30-80-40">12VAC30-80-40. </a><a href="http://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?000+reg+12VAC30-80-40">Feefor</a><a href="http://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?000+reg+12VAC30-80-40">-service providers: pharmacy.</a></p>'),
(218, '<p>lesser of the</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. 340B ceiling price (WAC50% if 340B ceiling price not available)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. 340B AAC.</p>', '<p>Low volume (0- 34,999 annual prescriptions): $15.69</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High volume (35,000+ annual prescriptions): $10.51</p>', '<p>340B ceiling price refers to the maximum amount a manufacturer can charge a covered entity for the purchase of a covered outpatient drug through the 340B Program. The 340B ceiling price is statutorily defined as the Average Manufacturer Price (AMP) reduced by the rebate percentage, which is commonly referred to as the Unit Rebate Amount (URA).</p>', '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</p>', 39, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-19 08:00:12', '2018-11-20 12:47:02', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(219, '<p>N/A</p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '<p>Wisconsin&rsquo;s Medicaid program, Bager Care, does not reimburse contract pharmacies for 340B drugs.</p>', '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</p>', 39, 1, 2, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-19 08:01:13', '2018-11-20 12:47:34', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(220, '<p>the lesser of</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Wholesale Acquisition Cost (WAC)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. State Maximum Allowed Cost (SMAC), if available, or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. the billed amount.</p>', '<p>Low volume (0- 34,999 annual prescriptions): $15.69</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High volume (35,000+ annual prescriptions): $10.51</p>', NULL, '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drug</p>', 39, 1, 3, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-19 08:02:55', '2018-11-20 12:48:12', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drug</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(221, '<p>the lesser of</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Wholesale Acquisition Cost (WAC)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. State Maximum Allowed Cost (SMAC), if available, or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. the billed amount</p>', '<p>Low volume (0- 34,999 annual prescriptions): $15.6</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9 High volume (35,000+ annual prescriptions): $10.51</p>', NULL, '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drug</p>', 39, 1, 4, '1', '1', '1', '2018-11-19 08:03:54', '2018-11-20 12:48:53', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drug</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(222, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Claims-level Indicators:</strong><br />\r\n&ldquo;the compound and noncompound drug claim formats will require submission clarification codes in order to identify claims for drugs purchased through the 340B Program. ForwardHealth will use the submission clarification code value to ensure appropriate rebate processes and avoid duplicate discounts.&rdquo;<br />\r\n&bull; &ldquo;&ldquo;20&rdquo; (340B) &mdash; Providers who submit a compound or noncompound drug claim for a drug purchased through the 340B Program will be required to enter submission clarification code &ldquo;20&rdquo; to indicate that the provider determined the drug being billed on the claim was purchased pursuant to rights available under Section 340B of the Public Health Act of 1992. ForwardHealth will use the submission clarification code value of &ldquo;20&rdquo; to apply 340B reimbursement and to ensure that only eligible claims are being used to obtain drug manufacturer rebates&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;Professional claim formats will require a &ldquo;UD&rdquo; modifier in order to identify claims for drugs purchased through the 340B Program.&rdquo;</p>', '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs<br />\r\nClaims for Drugs Purchased Through the 340B Drug Pricing Program</p>', 39, 1, 5, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-19 08:14:01', '2018-11-20 12:49:37', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</a><br />\r\n<a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/WIPortal/Subsystem/KW/Print.aspx?ia=1&amp;p=1&amp;sa=48&amp;s=4&amp;c=13&amp;nt=Claims%20for%20Drugs%20Purchased%20Through%20the%20340B%20Drug%20Pricing%20Program&amp;adv=Y">Claims for Drugs Purchased Through the 340B Drug Pricing Program</a></p>'),
(224, NULL, NULL, '<p>Wisconsin&rsquo;s Medicaid program, Bager, does not reimburse contract pharmacies for 340B drugs.</p>', '<p>ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</p>', 39, 1, 6, '1', '2', '1', '2018-11-19 08:15:13', '2018-11-20 12:50:17', '<p><a href="https://www.forwardhealth.wi.gov/kw/pdf/2017-07.pdf">ForwardHealth Update 2017-07 - Changes to Billing and Reimbursement Policy for Covered Outpatient Drugs</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
