(85, 'Yes', 'Telemedicine services provided to Medicaid members at an Indian Health Service (IHS)or tribal 638 health facility are reimbursed at the IHS/638 per encounter AIR rate , whereas services provided to Medicaid members at a non-IHS/638 facility are reimbursed at the capped FFS rate. There is no difference between in-person and telemedicine AIR and FFS capped rates.\n\nThe AIR rate reimburses providers for encounters, whereas the FFS rate reimburses for specific services.', 'AHCCS Telehealth Policy.', 'https://www.azahcccs.gov/PlansProviders/Downloads/IHS-TribalManual/IHSTelehealthTrainingManual.pdf', '1', 23, 1, 10, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:19', '2018-11-22 16:41:49'),
