(149, 'The Colorado Telehealth Network (CTN) administers federal dollars to aid eligible health care entities, especially in underserved regions of the state, to gain access to broadband connectivity to provide health care services in their communities. CTN leverages an annual $400 million federal fund to administer these subsidies through 3 programs: CTN 1, Net Connect and Building Communities. Additionally, CTN facilities the Colorado Telehealth Alliance (CTA) and participates in the State Innovation Model (SIM).', 'The   Colorado Telehealth Alliance aims to inform, educate and promote the adoption of telehealth across Colorado and offers its members several services, including educational meetings and workshops, networking, and updates on state and national telehealth regulations.', 'Colorado Telehealth Network', 'http://cotelehealth.com/', '1', 42, 1, 24, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:24', '2018-11-22 16:41:49'),
