(226, 'Telemedicine is the use of medical information exchange from one site to another via electronic communications to improve patientâ€™s health status. It is the use of two-way, real time interactive communication equipment to exchange the patient information from one site to another via an electronic communication system. This includes audio and video communications equipment. Closely associated with telemedicine is the term â€œtelehealth,â€ which is often used to encompass a broader definition of remote healthcare that does not always involve clinical services. Telehealth is the use of telecommunications technologies for clinical care (telemedicine), patient teachings and home health, health professional education (distance learning), administrative and program planning, and other diverse aspects of a health care delivery system. ', NULL, 'GA Department of Community Health, GA Medicaid Telemedicine Guidance, (Jan. 2018). ', 'https://www.mmis.georgia.gov/portal/Portals/0/StaticContent/Public/ALL/HANDBOOKS/Telemedicine%20Guidance_02262018%2020180226194618.pdf', '1', 64, 1, 1, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:29', '2018-11-22 16:41:49'),
(227, 'Yes', 'A provider must have a relationship with a patient prior to administering services via telemedicine,  unless  the provider: \n(1) Is providing care at the request of a physician, physician assistant or advanced practice registered nurse licensed in Georgia who has personally seen and examined the patient; or\n(2) Is providing care at the request of a Public Health Nurse, a Public School Nurse, the Department of Family and Childrenâ€™s Services, law enforcement, community mental health center or through an established child advocacy center for the protection or a minor, and the physician, physician assistant or advanced practice registered nurse is able to examine the patient using technology and peripherals that are equal or superior to an examination done personally by a provider within that providerâ€™s standard of care; or \n(3) Is able to examine the patient using technology and peripherals that are equal or superior to an examination done personally by a provider within that providerâ€™s standard of care.', 'GA Rule 360-3-.07.', 'https://medicalboard.georgia.gov/sites/medicalboard.georgia.gov/files/related_files/site_page/Adopted%20Telemedicine%20Rule.pdf', '1', 64, 1, 2, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:29', '2018-11-22 16:41:49'),
