(351, 'Law: "Telemedicine" means the delivery of health care services using electronic communications and information technology, including:\n(1) secure videoconferencing;\n(2) interactive audio-using store and forward technology; or\n(3) remote patient monitoring technology; between a provider in one (1) location and a patient in another location. \n\nMedicaid: Telemedicine services are defined as the use of videoconferencing equipment to allow a medical provider to render an exam or other service to a patient at distant location. Telehealth services are defined as the scheduled remote monitoring of clinical data through technologic equipment in the memberâ€™s home. ', NULL, 'IC 25-1-9.5 \n\nIndiana Health Coverage Programs: Telemedicine and Telehealth Services ', 'https://statecodesfiles.justia.com/indiana/2017/title-25/article-1/chapter-9.5/chapter-9.5.pdf    |\n\nhttp://provider.indianamedicaid.com/media/155583/telemedicine%20and%20telehealth%20services.pdf ', '0', 99, 1, 1, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:37', NULL),
(352, 'Yes', 'Provider-patient relationship established by:\n â€¢ Obtain patient\'s name and contact info; verbal statement or other data from patient identifying the location and identify of the patient (as is reasonable)\nâ€¢ Disclose prescriber\'s name and whether the prescriber is a physician, PA, advnaced practice RN, optometrist, or podistrist\nâ€¢ Obtain informed consent from patient\nâ€¢ Obtain patient\'s medical history and other info to establish diagnosis\nâ€¢ Discuss with the patient: diagnosis; evidence for diagnosis; risks/benefits of various treatment options, including when advisable to seek in-person care\nâ€¢ Create and maintain a medical record for the patient and, subject to the consent of the patient, notify the patient\'s primary care provider of any prescriptions the prescriber has issued for the patient if the primary care provider\'s contact information is provided by the patient. The requirements in this subdivision do not apply when any of the following are met: (A) The prescriber is using an electronic health record system that the patient\'s primary care provider is authorized to access; (B) The prescriber has established an ongoing provider-patient relationship with the patient by providing care to the patient at least two (2) consecutive times through the use of telemedicine services. If the conditions of this clause are met, the prescriber shall maintain a medical record for the patient and shall notify the patient\'s primary care provider of any issued prescriptions.Issue proper instructions for appropriate follow-up care.\nâ€¢ Issue proper instructions for appropriate follow-up care\nâ€¢ Provide a telemedicine visit summary to the patient, including information that indicates any prescription that is being prescribed', 'IC 25-1-9.5 ', 'https://statecodesfiles.justia.com/indiana/2017/title-25/article-1/chapter-9.5/chapter-9.5.pdf', '1', 99, 1, 2, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:37', '2018-11-22 16:41:49'),
