(369, 'Yes', 'According to the Oct 2017 IN Medicaid Telemedicine and Telehelath Services Manual, the IHCP reimburses for telemedicine services only when the following conditions are met:\nThe hub and spoke sites are greater than 20 miles apart, except for the following providers, which have no distance requirements:\nâ€“ Federally qualified health centers (FQHCs)\nâ€“ Rural health clinics (RHCs)\nâ€“ Community mental health centers (CMHCs)\nâ€“ Critical access hospitals (CAHs) \n\nHowever Indiana Code 12-15-5-11-e issued  directive requesting the elimination of distance restrictions on providers of telehealth services or telemedicine services within the Medicaid program. At the time of publication, the requirements had not yet changed.', 'Indiana Health Coverage Programs: Telemedicine and Telehealth Services ', 'http://provider.indianamedicaid.com/media/155583/telemedicine%20and%20telehealth%20services.pdf ', '0', 104, 1, 19, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:38', NULL),
