(545, 'Yes', 'Covered telemedicine services:\n â€¢ ESRD-related services\nâ€¢ Behavior change intervention\nâ€¢ Behavioral Health and/or Substance Use Disorder Treatment\nâ€¢ Education Services, Telehealth\nâ€¢ Inpatient consultations\nâ€¢ Nursing facility subsequent care\nâ€¢ Office or other outpatient consultations\nâ€¢ Office or other outpatient services\nâ€¢ Psychiatric diagnostic procedures\nâ€¢ Subsequent hospital care\nâ€¢ Training service â€“ Diabetes (Refer to the Diabetes Self-Management Education (DSME) Training Program subsection in the Hospital Chapter for specific program requirements)\n\n"Where face-to-face visits are required (such as ESRD and nursing facility related services), the telemedicine service may be used in addition to the required face-to-face visit, but cannot be used as a substitute. There must be at least one face-to-face hands-on visit (i.e., not via telemedicine) by a physician, nurse practitioner, or physicianâ€™s assistant per month to examine the vascular site for ESRD services. The initial visit for nursing facility services must be face-to-face."', 'Michigan Medicaid Provider Manual', 'http://www.mdch.state.mi.us/dch-medicaid/manuals/MedicaidProviderManual.pdf', '1', 153, 1, 20, '1', '2018-11-12 12:08:49', '2018-11-22 16:41:50'),
