(1061, 'Yes', 'The patient site must be: an established medical site; a state mental health facility; or a state supported living center.\n\nIn order for a location to qualify as an established medical site, the key criteria are the availability and presence of: qualified staff, also referred to as â€œpatient site presenters,â€ who are health care professionals licensed or certified in Texas, such as a nurse, emergency medical technician (EMT), or pharmacist; sufficient technology and medical equipment to allow for an adequate physical evaluation, as appropriate for the patientâ€™s presenting complaint; and sufficient size to accommodate patient privacy and to enable the presentation of the patient to the provider.\n\nContingent upon the locations meeting the above criteria, they could include a nurseâ€™s station in a public or private school, volunteer fire department, Emergency Medical Services station, oil rig, Mental Health and Mental Retardation Centers (MHMRs), Community Centers, pharmacy, or even a patientâ€™s home.\n\nIn the case of a patientâ€™s home, the rules further specify that a patient site presenter must use â€sufficient communication and remote medical diagnostic technologyâ€ to allow the provider to â€œcarry out an adequate physical examination appropriate for the patientâ€™s presenting condition while seeing and hearing the patient in real time.â€', NULL, NULL, '0', 297, 1, 11, '1', '2018-11-12 12:09:22', NULL),
(1062, 'Yes', 'Eligible distant site providers:\nâ€¢ Physician\nâ€¢ Certified Nutrition Specialist\nâ€¢ Nurse Practitioner\nâ€¢ Physician Assistant\nâ€¢ Certified Nurse Midwife\nâ€¢ Licensed professional counselors\nâ€¢ Licensed marriage and family therapist\nâ€¢ Licensed clinical social worker\nâ€¢ Psychologist\nâ€¢ Licensed psychological associate\nâ€¢ Provisionally licensed psychologist\nâ€¢ Licensed dietician\n', 'Texas Medicaid Provider Procedures Manual - Telecommunications Services Handbook', 'http://www.tmhp.com/Manuals_HTML1/TMPPM/Current/index.html?rhhlterm=telemedicine&rhsyns=%20#t=TMPPM%2F2_Telecommunication_Srvs%2F2_Telecommunication_Srvs.htm%3Frhhlterm%3Dtelemedicine%26rhsyns%3D%20', '1', 298, 1, 12, '1', '2018-11-12 12:09:22', '2018-11-22 16:41:50'),
