(108, 3, 'AZ', 'Question', 'Does the state Medicaid program reimburse telemedicine services at the same rate as services delivered in-person?', 'Yes', 'Telemedicine services provided to Medicaid members at an Indian Health Service (IHS)or tribal 638 health facility are reimbursed at the IHS/638 per encounter AIR rate , whereas services provided to Medicaid members at a non-IHS/638 facility are reimbursed at the capped FFS rate. There is no difference between in-person and telemedicine AIR and FFS capped rates.\n\nThe AIR rate reimburses providers for encounters, whereas the FFS rate reimburses for specific services.', 'AHCCS Telehealth Policy.', 'https://www.azahcccs.gov/PlansProviders/Downloads/IHS-TribalManual/IHSTelehealthTrainingManual.pdf', '2018-11-26 08:21:02', '2018-11-26 08:21:02'),
