(302, 10, 'GA', 'Question', 'Does the state limit Medicaid reimbursement for telemedicine services based on patient setting (e.g., where the patient is located at the time of a telemedicine encounter)?', 'Yes', 'Eligible originating sites include:\nâ€¢ Physician and Practitionerâ€™s Offices;\nâ€¢ Hospitals;\nâ€¢ Rural Health Clinics;\nâ€¢ Federally Qualified Health Centers;\nâ€¢ Hospital-based or CAH-based Renal Dialysis Centers (Independent Renal Dialysis Facilities are not eligible originating sites);\nâ€¢ Skilled Nursing Facilities (SNFs);\nâ€¢ Local Education Authorities and School Based Clinics;\nâ€¢ County Boards of Health;\nâ€¢ Emergency Medical Services Ambulances; and\nâ€¢ Pharmacies', 'GA Department of Community Health, GA Medicaid Telemedicine Guidance, (Jan. 2018). ', 'https://www.mmis.georgia.gov/portal/Portals/0/StaticContent/Public/ALL/HANDBOOKS/Telemedicine%20Guidance_02262018%2020180226194618.pdf', '2018-11-26 08:21:02', '2018-11-26 08:21:02'),
