(304, 10, 'GA', 'Question', 'Does the state limit Medicaid reimbursement for telemedicine services based on the type of provider facilitating the telemedicine encounter?', 'Yes', 'Practitioners at the distant site who may furnish and receive payment for covered telehealth services (subject to State law) are:\nâ€¢ Physicians;\nâ€¢ Nurse practitioners (NPs);\nâ€¢ Physician assistants (PAs);\nâ€¢ Nurse-midwives;\nâ€¢ Clinical nurse specialists (CNSs);\nâ€¢ Certified registered nurse anesthetists;\nâ€¢ Clinical psychologists (CPs) and clinical social workers (CSWs). CPs and CSWs cannot bill for psychiatric diagnostic interview examinations with medical services or medical evaluation and management services under Medicare. These practitioners may not bill or receive payment for Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) codes 90792, 90833, 90836, and 90838;\nâ€¢ Registered dietitians or nutrition professionals; and\nâ€¢ Speech Language Pathologists.', 'GA Department of Community Health, GA Medicaid Telemedicine Guidance, (Jan. 2018). ', 'https://www.mmis.georgia.gov/portal/Portals/0/StaticContent/Public/ALL/HANDBOOKS/Telemedicine%20Guidance_02262018%2020180226194618.pdf', '2018-11-26 08:21:02', '2018-11-26 08:21:02'),
