(436, 13, 'IL', 'Question', 'Does the state Medicaid program reimburse for telemedicine services provided via remote patient monitoring?', 'No', 'Exceptions:\n 1) Medicaid funds the use of home pregnancy monitoring devices for home uterine monitoring and pregnancy-induced hypertension monitoring (prior authorization required).\n\n2) The Older Adult Service Act (funded by the IL Dept. of Aging) provides funding for remote patient monitoring for adults ages 60+.', 'IL Department of Healthcare and Family Services, Handbook for Durable Medical Equipment \n\nOlder Adult Services Act (320 ILCS 42)', 'https://www.illinois.gov/hfs/SiteCollectionDocuments/m200.pdf\n\nhttp://www.ilga.gov/legislation/ilcs/ilcs3.asp?ActID=2630&ChapterID=31', '2018-11-26 08:21:03', '2018-11-26 08:21:03'),
