(540, 17, 'KY', 'Question', 'Does the state Medicaid plan restrict or provide exceptions for services provided via telemedicine for end-stage renal disease or dialysis? (e.g., in-person check-ups between treatments)', 'Yes;  End-stage renal disease monitoring, assessment, or counseling consultations for a home dialysis recipient is covered:\n\n      1. A physician directly employed by a hospitalâ€™s outpatient department if the telehealth consultation is billed under the hospitalâ€™s outpatient departmentâ€™s NPI; or\n\n      2. An APRN directly employed by a hospitalâ€™s outpatient department if the telehealth consultation is billed under the hospitalâ€™s outpatient departmentâ€™s NPI.', NULL, 'Â Â 907 KAR 3:170', 'http://www.lrc.ky.gov/kar/907/003/170.htm', '2018-11-26 08:21:03', '2018-11-26 08:21:03'),
