(862, 33, 'NC', 'Question', 'Do state laws or regulations prohibit the corporate practice of medicine?', 'Yes', NULL, '41 N.C. Attâ€™y Gen. Op. 60 (Aug. 26, 1970); â€œConsent Order of Kevin Bernard Noonan, M.D.,â€ before the North Carolina Medical Board, stating that Dr. Noonan was employed to render medical care to patients by a general business corporation and â€œthus, engaged in the unauthorized practice of medicineâ€ and that since the corporate practice doctrine prohibits business corporations from practicing medicine, Dr. Noonan engaged in unprofessional conduct.', 'https://wwwapps.ncmedboard.org/Clients/NCBOM/Public/LicenseeInformation/Details.aspx?EntityID=61105&PublicFile=1', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
(863, 33, 'NC', 'Question', 'Details on innovative payment and service delivery models or other state programs that include telehealth.', 'The State aims to leverage its existing clinical coverage policies and enhance access for providers and beneficiaries to services delivered via telemedicine by:\nâ€¢ Increasing provider awareness, education and training by supporting the establishment of an independent, statewide telemedicine alliance;. (State is seeking $5 million in federal funds for start-up costs for the telemedicine alliance)                                                                                                                            â€¢ North Carolina seeks expenditure authority (up to $80 million) to establish a â€œTelemedicine Innovation Fundâ€ to\nsupport provider-PHP collaborations that test evidence-based telemedicine initiatives aligned with the Stateâ€™s\nquality strategy goals, such as chronic disease management, wellness promotion and high-value care.21      (e.g., pilots)', NULL, 'North Carolina Medicaid and NC Health Choice: Amended Section 11115 Demonstration Waiver Application', 'https://files.nc.gov/ncdhhs/documents/files/NC-Amended1115DemonstrationWaiverApplication_GovCooperLtr_20171120.pdf?PpFJgK3wwi.BFkdX4t6e5L8oSXK6_c8B', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
(864, 33, 'NC', 'Question', 'Relevant guidance related to telehealth or telemedicine within Medicaid Managed Care contracts from this state.', 'Managed care organizations will be encouraged to support the use of telemedicine as a tool for ensuring access to needed services; allowed to provide access to a service that is not available within the plan\'s network; be permitted to leverage telemedicine in meeting DHHSâ€™ network adequacy standards; be encouraged to implement pilots that test additional telemedicine strategies and will invite PHPs to propose innovative pilots related to telemedicine in their responses to DHHSâ€™ Medicaid managed care procurement.', 'State\'s Medicaid program is FFS and is transitioning to managed care. ', 'Strategic Plan for Improvement of Behavioral Health Services: Report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Service and Fiscal Research Division. North Carolina Department of Health and Human Services  ', 'https://files.nc.gov/ncdhhs/documents/files/SL%202016-94%2C%20Sect.%2012F.10%20and%20SL%202017-57%20Sect.%2011F.6%20Strategic%20Plan%20for%20Improvement%20of%20Behavioral%20Health%20Services%20.pdf?4SjY_N4YP3KadXXEuEOhGa0xQzXdBJwd', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
