(866, 34, 'ND', 'Question', 'How does the state define telemedicine?', 'Law :  "Telehealth"\n(1) Means the use of interactive audio, video, or other telecommunications\ntechnology that is used by a health care provider or health care facility at a distant site to deliver health services at an originating site and that is delivered over a secure connection that complies with the requirements of\nstate and federal laws.\n\n(2) Includes the use of electronic media for consultation relating to the health\ncare diagnosis or treatment of a patient in real time or through the use of store-and-forward technology.\n\n(3) Does not include the use of audio-only telephone, electronic mail, or facsimile transmissions. \n\n Medicaid:  "Telemedicine" is the use of interactive audio-video equipment to link practitioners and patients at different sites. Telemedicine involves two collaborating provider sites: an â€œoriginating siteâ€ and a â€œdistant siteâ€. The client/patient is located at the originating site and the practitioner enrolled with ND Medicaid is located at the distant provider site to provide those professional services allowed/reimbursed by ND Medicaid. ', NULL, 'North Dakota Century Code - Accident and Health Insurance \n26.1-36-09.15 \n\nNorth Dakota Medicaid Medical Policy \nSFN 85 (6-9-2010)  ', 'http://www.legis.nd.gov/cencode/t26-1c36.pdf#nameddest=26p1-36-09p15 |\n\nhttp://www.nd.gov/dhs/services/medicalserv/medicaid/docs/telemedicine-policy.pdf ', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
(867, 34, 'ND', 'Question', 'Must a provider establish a relationship with a patient prior to engaging with them via telemedicine? ', 'No', NULL, 'North Dakota Medicaid Medical Policy \nSFN 85 (6-9-2010)  ', 'http://www.nd.gov/dhs/services/medicalserv/medicaid/docs/telemedicine-policy.pdf ', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
(868, 34, 'ND', 'Question', 'Must a telepresenter or health care provider be present with a patient during a telemedicine encounter?', 'Yes', 'Requires the presence of an individual to assist with establishing and maintaining the connection to the distant practitioner and have the ability to respond to the needs of the member.', 'North Dakota Medicaid Medical Policy \nSFN 85 (6-9-2010)  ', 'http://www.nd.gov/dhs/services/medicalserv/medicaid/docs/telemedicine-policy.pdf ', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
