(958, 29, 'NH', 'Question', 'Do state laws or regulations prohibit the corporate practice of medicine?', 'Yes', 'New Hampshire expressly prohibits the corporate practice of dentistry and optometry. Language in the state\'s professional corporation statute could be the basis for a prohibition on other health care professions, including medicine. New Hampshire also expressly prohibits pharmacists from engaging in fee splitting. ', 'N.H. Rev. Stat. 294-A:1', NULL, '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
