(1222, 39, 'RI', 'Question', 'If applicable, what type of consent is required?', 'Not Sure', '"The agreement should be discussed with the patient to ensure his/her understanding of the guidelines. The agreement should include the following terms:\n\nâ€¢ Types of transmissions that will be permitted (prescription refills, appointment scheduling, patient education, etc.)\n\nâ€¢Circumstances when alternate forms of communication or office visits should be utilized \n\nâ€¢ Security measures, such as encryption of data, password protected screen savers and data files, or utilization of other reliable authentication techniques, as well as potential risks to privacy\n\nâ€¢ Hold harmless clause for information lost due to technical failures\n\nâ€¢ Requirement for express patient consent to forward patient-identifiable information to a third party\n\nâ€¢A statement noting that the patientâ€™s failure to comply with the agreement may result in the physician terminating the e-mail relationship"', 'RI Department of Health. Telemedicine. Accessed Feb 2018.', 'http://www.health.ri.gov/healthcare/about/telemedicine/', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
