(1262, 40, 'SC', 'Question', 'Does the state limit Medicaid reimbursement for telemedicine services based on patient setting (e.g., where the patient is located at the time of a telemedicine encounter)?', 'Yes', '\n"Covered referring sites include:\nâ€¢ The office of a physician or practitioner\nâ€¢ Hospital (Inpatient and Outpatient)\nâ€¢ Rural Health Clinics\nâ€¢ Federally Qualified Health Centers\nâ€¢ Community Mental Health Centers\nâ€¢ Public Schools\nâ€¢ Act 301 Behavioral Health Centers\n\nThe referring site is eligible to receive a facility fee ($14.96 per encounter)."\n', 'SC Health and Human Services Department. Physicians Provider Manual, p. 2-56 (Oct. 2017)', 'https://www.scdhhs.gov/internet/pdf/manuals/Physicians/Manual.pdf', '2018-11-26 08:21:04', '2018-11-26 08:21:04'),
